   Education and Outreach

   The materials gathered in these pages are aimed at K-12 teachers and
   students. For more information visit the Education pages on the old
   Galileo site.


   Teacher Resources Teacher Resources provides galileo resources for K-12
   teachers.
   Galileo Spacecraft Activities presents a wide variety of games,
   puzzles, and facts; educational entertainment
   Slide from the Educators Slide Set Products offers a variety of visual
   materials on the Galileo Spacecraft and it's findings; includes posters
   and slides
   SSEP Logo
   Events provides links to Galileo and NASA events for the public
   Galileo Probe Just for Kids has fun links for kids like Amazing Galileo
   Facts, and the Galileo Arrival Day song.

   [rule.gif]

   Galileo Front Coming Soon!
   A new interactive CD-ROM on Galileo and the exploration of Jupiter will
   be released in 2002. Please watch this link in the coming weeks for
   ordering information.
   Solar System Ambassador Program The Solar System Ambassadors Program is
   a public outreach program designed to work with motivated volunteers
   across the nation.
   NASA NASA and Other Resources provides educational links to NASA
   websites and other resources.
   National Science Teachers Association Learning Opportunities provides
   non-Galileo-specific links for opportunities, resources, and programs.

